《'''铃儿响叮当'''》（'''Jingle Bells'''）是全世界最著名<ref>Browne, Ray B. and Browne, Pat. [https://books.google.com/books?id=U3rJxPYT32MC&pg=PA171&dq=%22jingle+bells%22+%22best+known%22 ''The Guide to United States Popular Culture''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U3rJxPYT32MC&pg=PA171&dq=%22jingle+bells%22+%22best+known%22 |date=20160617185524 }} Popular Press, 2001. {{ISBN|0879728213}}. p.171</ref>并且最经常传唱<ref>Collins, Ace. [https://books.google.com/books?id=Q2xV3ZhqEFsC&q=%22jingle+bells%22+%22best+known%22+%22winter+song%22&dq=%22jingle+bells%22+%22best+known%22+%22winter+song%22 ''Stories Behind the Best-Loved Songs of Christmas''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Q2xV3ZhqEFsC&q=%22jingle+bells%22+%22best+known%22+%22winter+song%22&dq=%22jingle+bells%22+%22best+known%22+%22winter+song%22 |date=20160513090904 }} Zondervan, 2004. {{ISBN|0310264480}}. p.104.</ref>的美国冬季歌曲。它的作者是{{tsl|en|James Lord Pierpont|詹姆斯·洛德·皮爾龐特}} (1822–1893) 。这首歌发行于1857年秋天，原名One Horse Open Sleigh。虽然它现在一般与[[圣诞节|圣诞节]]联系在一起，但是它原来是用于庆祝[[感恩节|感恩节]]的<ref>{{cite web|title=Jingle Bells (Christmas Read-Aloud Stories, Carols, & more)|url=http://www.readersdigest.ca/christmas/kind_christmas/jingle_bells.html|publisher=Reader's Digest|accessdate=November 19, 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927205505/http://www.readersdigest.ca/christmas/kind_christmas/jingle_bells.html|archivedate=2007-09-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|journal=TIME|url=http://entertainment.time.com/2012/12/17/yule-laugh-yule-cry-10-things-you-didnt-know-about-beloved-holiday-songs/?iid=tl-article-recirc|title=Yule Laugh, Yule Cry: 10 Things You Didn’t Know About Beloved Holiday Songs|author=Wook Kim|date=December 17, 2012|access-date=2015-12-26|archive-date=2016-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116233535/http://entertainment.time.com/2012/12/17/yule-laugh-yule-cry-10-things-you-didnt-know-about-beloved-holiday-songs/?iid=tl-article-recirc|dead-url=no}} – [http://entertainment.time.com/2012/12/17/yule-laugh-yule-cry-10-things-you-didnt-know-about-beloved-holiday-songs/?iid=tl-article-recirc "Jingle Bells" (p. 2)] {{Wayback|url=http://entertainment.time.com/2012/12/17/yule-laugh-yule-cry-10-things-you-didnt-know-about-beloved-holiday-songs/?iid=tl-article-recirc |date=20160116233535 }}</ref>。它曾经被声称是写给[[主日學|主日學]]合唱团演唱的，但是历史学家对此有争议，因为在那个年代其歌词會被視為具“挑逗性”，不適合儿童教會合唱团<ref>{{cite web |title=A Thanksgiving Carol |url=http://www.snopes.com/holidays/christmas/music/jinglebells.asp |publisher=snopes.com |date=December 18, 2014 |accessdate=December 23, 2014 |archive-date=2019-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701184501/https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/jingle-bells-thanksgiving-carol/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

